RM  11717263
RT  Use of transposon Tn5367 mutagenesis and a nitroimidazopyran-based
RT  selection system to demonstrate a requirement for fbiA and fbiB in
RT  coenzyme F(420) biosynthesis by Mycobacterium bovis BCG.
RA  Choi KP, Bair TB, Bae YM, Daniels L;
RL  J Bacteriol. 2001;183:7058-7066.
CC  The chromophore of coenzyme F420 is
CC  7,8-didemethyl-8-hydroxy-5-deazaflavin, or FO, which is also used in a
CC  cyanobacterial DNA photoreactivating enzyme. Modification of FO to
CC  create coenzyme F420 includes the GTP-dependent addition of two
CC  glutamate residues in Methanococcus jannaschii and five or six in
CC  Mycobacterium bovis. CofF, which caps the gamma-glutamyl tail after two
CC  glutamates, occurs only the archaea.
**  MJ_1418 generates lactaldehyde  cofA (MJ_1411) generates L-lactate from
**  lactaldehyde  cofB uses GTP to make 2-phospho-L-lactate from L-lactate 
**  cofG (MJ_0446)  cofH (MJ_1431)  cofE (MJ_0768) = Nterm of FbiB (M.
**  bovis)  cofD (MJ_1256) = FbiA (M. bovis)  cofC (MJ_0887)  cofF
**  (MJ_1001)  It appears that Anacystis nidulans (e.g.) make the precursor
**  FO (the chromophore of F420) but not F420 itself.
